{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0b5c64fe-d9bf-4c47-838d-b4edfd44da9d","content":"This is a well-known issue. **.NET MAUI's Android build tooling expects to use the Microsoft OpenJDK 17** that ships with the `maui-android` workload — not a third-party JDK like Adoptium Temurin. Your `JAVA_HOME` is overriding the build's JDK selection and pointing it to an incompatible distribution.\n\n### Fix\n\n**Option A — Unset `JAVA_HOME`** so the build auto-discovers the workload-bundled JDK:\n\n```bash\nunset JAVA_HOME\n```\n\nRemove or comment out any `export JAVA_HOME=…` line in your `~/.zshrc` / `~/.bash_profile`.\n\n**Option B — Point `JAVA_HOME` to the Microsoft OpenJDK 17** installed by the workload:\n\n```bash\nexport JAVA_HOME=\"/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/microsoft-17.jdk/Contents/Home\"\n```\n\nYou can verify it's installed with:\n\n```bash\nls /Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/\n```\n\nIf `microsoft-17.jdk` is missing, reinstall the workload:\n\n```bash\ndotnet workload install maui-android\n```\n\n**Option C — Set `<JavaSdkDirectory>` in your `.csproj`** to explicitly pin it per-project:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup Condition=\"'$(TargetFramework)' == 'net8.0-android'\">\n  <JavaSdkDirectory>/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/microsoft-17.jdk/Contents/Home</JavaSdkDirectory>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nAfter any of these, rebuild with `dotnet build` and the Java error should be resolved.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7e186f01-7c62-4743-812e-f1080d6a5339","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository is empty or has no relevant files. Let me answer based on my knowledge of .NET MAUI and Java/JDK compatibility issues.\n\nThe key issue: .NET MAUI / Xamarin.Android ships with its own JDK (Microsoft OpenJDK 17) and uses it for Android builds. However, when JAVA_HOME is set to a different JDK (like Adoptium Temurin), it can cause conflicts.\n\nBut more specifically, the common issue with .NET MAUI Android builds and Java on macOS:\n\n1. .NET 8+ MAUI requires JDK 17\n\n\n2. The Android build tools bundled with MAUI expect Microsoft's OpenJDK 17 distribution specifically\n\nThe typical problem is that when JAVA_HOME points to a different JDK installation like Temurin, the build process encounters version mismatches or missing module errors because MAUI's Android SDK is configured to work with its own bundled JDK rather than external installations.\n\nThe core issue with Temurin specifically is that it may lack certain modules or have subtle differences in how it's built compared to what the Android tooling expects, particularly around signing and cryptographic functionality.\n\nThe solution typically involves either unsetting `JAVA_HOME` entirely so the build defaults to the workload-installed Microsoft OpenJDK, or explicitly pointing `JAVA_HOME` to the Microsoft JDK 17 that ships with the MAUI Android workload—which on macOS is usually located at `/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/microsoft-17.jdk/Contents/Home` or within the dotnet workload directory.\n\nNow I'm thinking through what specific Java error they might be encountering—likely something like `UnsupportedClassVersionError` if there's a Java version mismatch, or module-related failures if the JDK is missing expected components.\n\nThe core issue is probably that .NET MAUI on macOS expects to use its bundled Microsoft OpenJDK, and when `JAVA_HOME` points to a different JDK like Adoptium Temurin, the build fails because MAUI's Gradle configuration doesn't recognize or work with that alternative JDK distribution. The core issue is that .NET MAUI's Android workload ships with Microsoft OpenJDK 17, but when `JAVA_HOME` points to Temurin instead, the build fails because the Android SDK tools and Gradle expect the Microsoft distribution. I can resolve this by either redirecting `JAVA_HOME` to the Microsoft OpenJDK or unsetting it entirely to let the build locate it automatically, and I can help the user find the correct path using `dotnet android info` or checking the standard installation directory.","outputTokens":1731,"requestId":"77C1:176D78:7EF5CAB:8D240D4:69EABDFE"},"id":"07b7d632-31e4-452a-a5d2-667a74724451","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:49:36.309Z","parentId":"b4688b53-f2aa-440f-8080-aa351675e83a"}
